			<h3 class="first"><a href="#p34171">Duke Nukem Forever Demo</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><img src="./styles/new-life/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" />by <strong><span style="color: #AA0000;" class="username-coloured">Ace12GA</span></strong> on Mon Jun 06, 2011 11:14 pm </p>

			

			<div class="content">3 words - total let down. Really.<br /><br />Yes there is lots of interactivity, yes Duke says some seriously funny shit; however. The actual shooter mechanics are really poor. The driving mechanics are also poor. Reloading!? Poor graphics in the second demo level; no really. Poor design, dated graphics. Felt like a rail shooter for a little bit. Health system is lame.<br /><br />It still has some potential, but really not so good. I would not buy the game based on the demo alone, and with that in mind, there goes a lot of potential sales to players that never enjoyed the original Duke 3D.<br /><br />I guess it had no choice but to be a total let down after so long. A real shame though. I hope the full game is far more polished, and far better.<br /><br />What happened to the days of a demo that spanned the first segment of the full game? Doom, Doom II, Duke 3D, etc... This has just strayed too far from its roots. Did I mention you have to reload the guns!!! WTF, this isn't COD, its Duke Nukem!</div>

			

		</div>

		
