		<div class="postbody">
			

			<h3 ><a href="#p34185">Re: Duke Nukem Forever Demo</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><img src="./styles/new-life/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" />by <strong>rogue</strong> on Sun Jul 10, 2011 7:48 pm </p>

			

			<div class="content">i borrowed the full version from a friend because he warned me not to buy it. he was right.<br /><br />holy crap it's bad. really bad.<br /><br />the game would be bad even if this weren't duke fucking nukem, but since this actually is the game that we've been waiting for for more than 10 years it reaches painful levels of badness.<br /><br />sure, there are a few nice moments, references and callbacks to the original but they are completely overwhelmed by unbelievable amounts of annoying bullshit.<br /><br />a few highlights: new duke is a pussy. a few hits from a pigcop will kill you. if three of them manage to bumrush you, you're dead. combine this with the stupid checkpoint system (no quickload/save) and it gets annoying. then add the fact that duke apparently got old and can only carry two weapons at a time which means that you frequently have the wrong weapon or (even more frequently) not enough ammo and you're running the risk of an aneurysm.<br /><br />the level design is also horrible. a bunch of very linear crap with annoying boss battles or fight-waves-of-aliens-with-a-mounted-turret episodes thrown in. <br />gone are the open and (for the time) sprawling levels from the duke3d era. there is almost no opportunity to explore the levels and discover neat little gags thrown in by the designers which at least for me was a staple of duke3d.  <img src="./images/smilies/old1.gif" alt=":old:" title="" /> <br />instead you get a whole lot of dark corridors and industrial areas which feel somewhat like half-life, only not as fun.<br />there is also a wtf-inducing episode in an alien infested area. you run around in the dark a lot and roll giant glowing beetles around in order to open doors. you also encounter cocooned women which you have to kill before they give birth to baby aliens.<br /><br />the driving episodes are kinda fun but suffer from boring level design and pure repetitiveness. drive your monster truck around some brown desert, squish some aliens, jump over ramps a lot, run out of gas. run around a bit and find a gas can, refuel, repeat. it's not that bad, really, but it gets old fast. and of course the designers then decided to repeat that cycle like three or four times.<br /><br />though pretty much the worst is the strip club level. <br />yes, you get a strip club with topless dancers and a bunch of gambling machines (all of which can be used) but instead of having to defend the strippers from aliens like in the good old times you get sent on a mission to find a dildo, a condom and some popcorn.<br />and that's it. wtf?<br /><br />overall it feels like a bunch of disjointed crap, like leftovers from several attempts at making the game thrown together.<br /><br />i don't get it. they took their sweet time and finally managed to produce a game which is not only ugly and simply not fun but instead alternates between annoying and boring. how the hell do you manage to take a duke nukem game and make it boring?</div>

			

		</div>

		
